><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>S13ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34aff7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>a53d215e-c270-409d-bfb9-bb6623dfdd65</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>107</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b:94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af:f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing the Audit Logger Process</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Audit Logger may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to unauthorized access to Audit Log Store. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the source process.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary bidirectional</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S1</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>T183ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34aff7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>a53d215e-c270-409d-bfb9-bb6623dfdd65</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>108</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b:94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af:f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>The Audit Log Store Data Store Could Be Corrupted</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Data flowing across Binary bidirectional may be tampered with by an attacker. This may lead to corruption of Audit Log Store. Ensure the integrity of the data flow to the data store.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary bidirectional</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>T18</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>R83ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34aff7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>a53d215e-c270-409d-bfb9-bb6623dfdd65</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>109</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b:94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af:f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Store Denies Audit Log Store Potentially Writing Data</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Repudiation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Repudiation threats involve an adversary denying that something happened.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Audit Log Store claims that it did not write data received from an entity on the other side of the trust boundary. Consider using logging or auditing to record the source, time, and summary of the received data.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary bidirectional</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>R8</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>I63ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34aff7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>a53d215e-c270-409d-bfb9-bb6623dfdd65</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>110</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b:94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af:f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Flow Sniffing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Information Disclosure</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Information disclosure happens when the information can be read by an unauthorized party.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Data flowing across Binary bidirectional may be sniffed by an attacker. Depending on what type of data an attacker can read, it may be used to attack other parts of the system or simply be a disclosure of information leading to compliance violations. Consider encrypting the data flow.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary bidirectional</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>I6</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D43ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34aff7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>a53d215e-c270-409d-bfb9-bb6623dfdd65</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>111</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b:94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af:f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Flow Binary Is Potentially Interrupted</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Denial Of Service</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>An external agent interrupts data flowing across a trust boundary in either direction.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Binary bidirectional</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D4</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D53ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34aff7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>a53d215e-c270-409d-bfb9-bb6623dfdd65</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>112</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>3ad70b89-cbaa-46da-90af-60b39866725b:94d3f073-29ee-451b-afac-21abcbaa34af:f7ebb07c-e60a-4a98-8049-bfaa7a109a15</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Store Inaccessible</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring